  "response": "To prepare for IBPS PO 2015 within two months, follow this strategic approach:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Familiarize yourself with section-wise syllabus\n- Know marks distribution and time allocation\n- Practice previous year question papers\n\n2. Quantitative Aptitude\n- Focus on basic mathematics\n- Practice speed, time & work, percentages\n- Solve mock tests regularly\n- Time management is crucial\n\n3. Reasoning\n- Practice puzzle, coding-decoding\n- Blood relations\n- Sequence & series\n- Logical reasoning\n- Mock tests daily\n\n4. English Language\n- Read newspapers daily\n- Practice comprehension\n- Improve vocabulary\n- Grammar basics\n- Mock tests\n\n5. Computer Knowledge\n- Basic computer fundamentals\n- MS Office\n- Internet concepts\n- Online mock tests\n\n6. General Awareness\n- Current affairs\n- Banking awareness\n- Read newspapers\n- Monthly current affairs magazines\n\n7. Study Plan\n- 5-6 hours daily dedicated study\n- Divide time between subjects\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Analyze weak areas\n\n8. Additional Tips\n- Stay motivated\n- Maintain good health\n- Practice time management\n- Solve previous year papers\n\nConsistent practice and strategic preparation are key to success.",
